data.title: Travis Barker serenades wife Kourtney Kardashian in latest song 'Fell in Love'
data.meta_description: Travis Barker serenaded his 'rockstar wife' Kourtney Kardashian in front of the whole world, and she’s all for it.The smitten Kardashian star, 44, shared the lyrics from Blink-182’s...
data.text:
Travis Barker serenaded his 'rockstar wife' Kourtney Kardashian in front of the whole world, and she’s all for it.

The smitten Kardashian star, 44, shared the lyrics from Blink-182’s latest single, Fell in Love, which were partly penned by drummer Barker, drawing focus to the very sweet and suspiciously relevant-to-their-relationship chorus of the song.

Taking to her Instagram stories on Monday, the expecting mother posted a Spotify screen recording of her husband’s latest musical achievement, his ninth studio album entitled One More Time.

"Do you remember the time when we first met?/ You were at a party with your ex/ I said hello, then I got drunk/ Do you remember the time we fell in love?" vocalists DeLonge and Hoppus sung the lyrics partly penned by Barker.

Notably, Barker not only co-wrote but almost entirely produced the album, per an interview with The Zane Lane posted on October 18th.

Whether or not they actually reflect real life events, the lyrics definitely struck a chord with Kourtney, who met her husband-of-one year and the father of her unborn child over a decade ago, while she was involved with now ex, Scott Disick, per a relationship timeline by US Weekly.

The Poosh founder and the musician then sparked dating rumours in 2018, three years into Kourtney and Scott’s post-divorce co-parenting relationship.

Fast forward to today, Kourtney is living her best "rockstar world tour wife" life, as she referred to herself in an old Instagram post from last year.
